Web Application:

Before creating a flask application, a virtual environment needs to be created. 

Creating a virtual enrivonment in Python
python -m venv virtual #virtual is the name of the virtual folder



Book Manager applications:
sqllite3 
- Python library to interact with SQLLite database. SQL code can be written inside python using sqllite3
- This is not the actual SQLLite database. SQLLite database can be created as a file and hence this application can be distributed to anyone without having to install sqllite. 

psycopg2

1. Connect to a database
2. Create a cursor object
3. Write a Sql query
4. Commit changes
5. Close the connection


psycopg2 dependencies
sudo apt install -y build-essential libssl-dev libffi-dev python3-dev libjpeg-dev libjpeg8-dev
sudo apt install libpq-dev
sudo apt-get install python3-pip
pip install psycopg2
